Skibbe joins Voller with contract extension until 2006 
German national team assistant manager Michael Skibbe has extended his
contract with the German Football Federation (DFB) until the 2006 World
Cup, the DFB announced here Monday.
Skibbe, whose contract was due to expire in 2004, will busy himself
with the search for young talent as assistant to Germany manager Rudi
Voller who on December 6 also extended his contract with the DFB until
2006.
The 2006 World Cup will be held in Germany.
